Package org.forgerock.openam.radius.server.monitoring

Interface RadiusServerEventMonitorMXBean

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RadiusServerEventRegistrar
    public interface RadiusServerEventMonitorMXBean
    An interface to expose the state of the RADIUS server to a JMX client such as visualVM or JConsole.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      long getNumberOfAcceptedPackets()
      get the number of packets accepted by the radius server.
      long getNumberOfAuthRequestsAccepted()
      get the number of auth requests (AccessRequest packets) that resulted in AccessAccept packets being returned in response to the request.
      long getNumberOfAuthRequestsRejected()
      get the number of auth requests (AccessRequest packets) that resulted in AccessReject packets being returned in response to the request.
      long getNumberOfPacketsProcessed()
      get the number of packets processed by the radius server (since started).
      long getNumberOfPacketsRecieved()
      Get a long count of all of the RADIUS packets received on the UDP channel.

    • Method Detail

      • getNumberOfPacketsRecieved

        long getNumberOfPacketsRecieved()
        Get a long count of all of the RADIUS packets received on the UDP channel.
        Returns:
        a long count of all of the RADIUS packets received on the UDP channel.

      • getNumberOfAcceptedPackets

        long getNumberOfAcceptedPackets()
        get the number of packets accepted by the radius server. These are packets that were understood and hence not thrown away or ignored by the RADIUS server.
        Returns:
        a long indicating the no. of packets understood and accepted.

      • getNumberOfPacketsProcessed

        long getNumberOfPacketsProcessed()
        get the number of packets processed by the radius server (since started). These packets may have led to auth or been denied auth, but they were processed to completion, and hence not dropped, or failed in some way.
        Returns:
        a long indicating the number of packets processed.

      • getNumberOfAuthRequestsAccepted

        long getNumberOfAuthRequestsAccepted()
        get the number of auth requests (AccessRequest packets) that resulted in AccessAccept packets being returned in response to the request.
        Returns:
        a long indicating the number of requests that resulted in acceptance.

      • getNumberOfAuthRequestsRejected

        long getNumberOfAuthRequestsRejected()
        get the number of auth requests (AccessRequest packets) that resulted in AccessReject packets being returned in response to the request.
        Returns:
        a long indicating the number of requests that resulted in rejection.
